The Vice President, Mike Pence, gave a speech at Nellis Air Force Base in Las Vegas, Nevada, praising the men and women of the armed forces for their dedication and service. He emphasized the importance of the military in protecting the nation and its allies, and assured them that President Trump supports them. Pence also discussed the current global threats, including radical Islamic terrorism and the regime in North Korea, and expressed confidence in the capabilities of the US Armed Forces to defend the country. He called on Congress to provide the necessary resources and support to strengthen the military. Pence concluded by thanking the audience for their service and assuring them of the prayers and support of the American people.